Every time we are confused about anything or in a dilemma or unsure, we can go back to and rely on the virtues. Gratitude. Courage. Meekness. Knowledge. It brings me great joy even to just continuously name them. One always must examine if what he says embodies these dispositions

Still I am wary not to trivialize them. The desert fathers said you should focus on cultivating just one in specific for decades to fully acquire its spiritual riches. On the other hand as Cioran pointed out vices are always "sticky" together and one drags the other by its chain.
